# Cloud Build source upload filter
#
# Without this file, ``gcloud builds submit`` would fall back to
# ``.gitignore`` — which covers most of the large dirs but misses
# a few build artefacts that are under git-tracked parents. List
# every heavy path here explicitly so the source tarball stays
# small and Cloud Build submissions finish in seconds, not minutes.

# Version control + CI state
.git/
.github/

# Python virtual environments + caches
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.hypothesis/

# Rust build artefacts — these are the single largest thing
# ``.gitignore`` misses. Cargo creates multi-GB target trees.
**/target/
**/Cargo.lock.bak

# Node / bundler artefacts (demo directory)
**/node_modules/
**/dist/

# MkDocs build output
site/

# Benchmark result JSON — regenerated on every run, no need to
# ship prior results into the container image
benchmarks/results/*
!benchmarks/results/SCHEMA.md
benchmarks/models/
benchmarks/.cache/

# HuggingFace / PyTorch model caches
.cache/
~/.cache/huggingface/
ckpts/
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.bin

# Local notebooks' checkpoint dirs
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# IDE + OS detritus
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp

# Session logs, internal docs, credentials — never enter a
# container we might ship or share later
.coordination/
docs/internal/
.claude/
CLAUDE.md
.agent_metadata.json

# Training artefacts — ``training/output/`` alone is 45 GB,
# ``training/data*/`` adds another ~8 GB of model checkpoints
# and datasets that the container does NOT need. Mirror the
# gitignore whitelist pattern: exclude everything, then re-add
# just the files the build context actually requires.
/training/*
!/training/Dockerfile.distil
!/training/Dockerfile.benchmarks
!/training/distil_v5_cloud.py
!/training/distil_factcg.py
!/training/launch_cloud.sh
!/training/run_vertex.sh
!/training/requirements-distil.in
!/training/requirements-distil.txt

/models/
MODELS/
BACKUP/
ARCHIVE/

# backfire-kernel build dirs that are NOT in .gitignore —
# cargo's target tree is the big one; dist/ holds compiled wheels.
backfire-kernel/target/
backfire-kernel/dist/
backfire-kernel/**/*.rlib
backfire-kernel/**/*.rmeta

# Nohup + stray logs
*.log
nohup.out
logs/
